76561197983601366,Recommended,265990,9721759,"Posted: 4 April, 2014",all,William Shakeshack,"Rogue's Tale is a roguelike in the vein of the older roguelikes instead of the many new ""roguelites"".First of all this game might not be for anyone, the content is randomly generated each playthrough like in many roguelikes. Although this one can be quite unforgiving, being oneshotted at the spawn point is not a rarety. You can play really well for an hour but die horribly in 3 turns. Death is always lurking in each corner and it adds a lot of tension, especially if you advance far into the game. This fact might be really offputting for some people because sometimes you just can't do anything to evade death.As you progress through the dungeon you gain loot and supplies which you use to survive on your journey. It's all fairly standard without adding anything new. I think this is a strong point of Rogue's Tale, it's just a really nice roguelike without any fancy twists. It's really addictive and you always want to try your luck again.The major aspect that I dislike is the somewhat cumbersome controls, they are not intuitive and there are many keys that could have been merged together. Nevertheless you get used to it fairly quickly. The graphics and sound effects do their job, it's a nice tile based rougelike. Although I wished there was more variety in the music.I recommend it to anyone who likes more oldschoold and hard roguelikes if you can bear the random nature of the game."
